<section class="page-header">
<h2>Get in Touch</h2>
<p>Questions, research requests, volunteer inquiries, artifact offers, and local stories are welcome.</p>
</section>

<section class="cards">
<div class="card">
<h3>Location</h3>
<p>Salvage Fisherman's Museum<br>52 Mountainview Rd<br>Salvage, NL, A0G 0J2</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Research and Genealogy</h3>
<p>Ask staff or volunteers about church records, family history resources, photographs, and local history files available at the museum.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Donations and Loans</h3>
<p>Please contact the museum before bringing artifacts, documents, or photographs so the committee can review how they fit the collection.</p>
<p class="email-line"><a href="mailto:salvagefishermansmuseum@gmail.com">salvagefishermansmuseum@gmail.com</a></p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="content">
<h2>Before You Visit</h2>
<p>The museum is open seasonally and admission is by donation. Visitors are encouraged to sign the guest book, ask questions, browse the gift shop, and explore outdoor storyboards around Salvage.</p>

<div class="note">
<h3>Contact Details</h3>
<p>Email <a href="mailto:salvagefishermansmuseum@gmail.com">salvagefishermansmuseum@gmail.com</a> for museum questions, research requests, donations, loans, or volunteer inquiries.</p>
</div>
</section>

<footer>
<p>Salvage Fisherman's Museum</p>
